1
00:00:14,356 --> 00:00:19,794
<i>Connecting old words</i>
<i>that have been used up</i>

2
00:00:20,629 --> 00:00:28,536
<i>I just want to convey</i>
<i>my simple thoughts</i>

3
00:00:28,603 --> 00:00:33,973
<i>That day's faint wind blows away</i>

4
00:00:34,042 --> 00:00:38,103
<i>at the castle ruins of yesterday</i>

5
00:00:39,348 --> 00:00:44,251
<i>I'll laugh with you</i>
<i>and live for the moment</i>

6
00:00:44,987 --> 00:00:51,893
<i>Still that incident</i>
<i>will continue to trouble you, right?</i>

7
00:00:53,295 --> 00:00:56,787
<i>That's why it must be good bye</i>

8
00:00:56,865 --> 00:01:03,771
<i>Leaving nothing behind,</i>
<i>let us share what is left</i>

9
00:01:03,905 --> 00:01:10,970
<i>In time, we'll realize</i>
<i>that it was everything</i>

10
00:01:11,046 --> 00:01:17,713
<i>And sadness will touch our cheeks,</i>
<i>creating a river of tears</i>

11
00:01:18,120 --> 00:01:27,688
<i>Trembling thoughts swept into a vortex</i>
<i>and melting away</i>

12
00:01:39,418 --> 00:01:45,414
<i>The Beast Within</i>

13
00:01:52,398 --> 00:01:53,763
Sasuke!

14
00:01:54,733 --> 00:01:55,791
Why...?!

15
00:01:56,301 --> 00:01:58,565
Why do you run away?!

16
00:01:59,471 --> 00:02:00,597
Sasuke!

17
00:02:26,432 --> 00:02:27,865
Don't...

18
00:02:28,233 --> 00:02:29,791
be staring at...

19
00:02:31,437 --> 00:02:32,131
people!

20
00:02:40,879 --> 00:02:42,278
<i>He's faster than earlier!</i>

21
00:02:49,855 --> 00:02:51,516
<i>The medicine from earlier...</i>

22
00:02:52,157 --> 00:02:55,320
<i>Was there some kind of</i>
<i>special ingredient in it or something...?</i>

23
00:02:57,663 --> 00:03:00,598
Not... bad...

24
00:03:03,368 --> 00:03:08,965
Moving around kind of...
made me feel super weird...

25
00:03:09,141 --> 00:03:09,869
Oh, my...!

26
00:03:19,218 --> 00:03:21,584
<i>What was that...all of a sudden...?</i>

27
00:03:26,125 --> 00:03:28,423
<i>Did he really...fall asleep...?</i>

28
00:03:37,536 --> 00:03:39,265
You fell for it, eh?!

29
00:03:43,709 --> 00:03:48,544
It looked like I was sleeping,
but actually I wasn't!

30
00:03:49,114 --> 00:03:51,981
This is the Shinobi secret...!

31
00:03:52,551 --> 00:03:56,681
Guy Sensei... I did it!

32
00:04:00,592 --> 00:04:05,689
Guy Sensei... I... I...

33
00:04:20,746 --> 00:04:23,840
You fell for it yet again, huh?!
Hey!

34
00:04:24,817 --> 00:04:29,845
You're sorely mistaken
if you think I'm the kind of person

35
00:04:29,922 --> 00:04:32,186
to sleep spread eagle
in a place like this!

36
00:04:34,026 --> 00:04:37,325
I... I...

37
00:04:38,831 --> 00:04:46,260
What...? What am I doing
in a place like this...?

38
00:04:53,045 --> 00:04:54,012
What...?

39
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:57,774
Why...? Why...?

40
00:05:10,929 --> 00:05:11,861
<i>Alcohol...?</i>

41
00:05:12,731 --> 00:05:14,790
<i>He's just drunk, huh...?</i>

42
00:05:16,168 --> 00:05:21,902
If so... I'll send you to another world
before you can even feel pain...

43
00:05:53,005 --> 00:05:56,941
<i>Damn it...</i>
<i>I don't have enough Chakra...</i>

44
00:05:57,776 --> 00:05:59,141
<i>At this rate...</i>

45
00:06:21,166 --> 00:06:23,361
<i>As might be expected,</i>
<i>things will get hairy</i>

46
00:06:23,435 --> 00:06:25,164
<i>if I stay in the water any longer</i>
<i>with this wound...</i>

47
00:07:29,668 --> 00:07:31,158
<i>Why won't it hit?!</i>

48
00:07:33,005 --> 00:07:35,906
And here I was sleeping comfortably...

49
00:07:38,410 --> 00:07:40,708
You're a buzzing, annoying fly!

50
00:07:46,693 --> 00:07:52,893
Hey! Bring it on! Hey c'mon...
I'll show you...

51
00:07:53,992 --> 00:07:57,120
<i>What're...those movements...?</i>

52
00:07:58,630 --> 00:08:01,690
As you know, in that technique...

53
00:08:01,767 --> 00:08:05,760
one gets stronger the more one drinks
and the more one gets drunk.

54
00:08:08,340 --> 00:08:09,602
I know...

55
00:08:09,941 --> 00:08:11,568
At the restaurant before...

56
00:08:11,710 --> 00:08:16,670
When Lee mistook it for water
and drank a small cup of alcohol...

57
00:08:32,297 --> 00:08:37,291
It took Neji and me, the both of us,
to finally... be able to overpower Lee.

58
00:08:40,772 --> 00:08:43,673
You couldn't restrain him yourself...?

59
00:08:43,775 --> 00:08:47,711
I could overpower him
if I was fighting him as an enemy...

60
00:08:47,779 --> 00:08:52,079
But well, I couldn't inflict a serious injury
on my beloved student...

61
00:08:52,951 --> 00:08:54,043
That's right...

62
00:08:54,419 --> 00:08:57,616
That's how it was
just with one small cup, so...

63
00:08:58,623 --> 00:09:02,389
If he were to drink
an entire bottle of alcohol...

64
00:09:03,095 --> 00:09:05,563
An invincible strength, huh...?

65
00:09:06,698 --> 00:09:09,360
But it's just after
he got out of the hospital.

66
00:09:10,335 --> 00:09:12,326
How long will his body
hold on for...?

67
00:09:22,047 --> 00:09:25,949
<i>A Loopy Fist User, huh...?</i>
<i>It's my first time seeing one...</i>

68
00:09:26,651 --> 00:09:31,611
If you're not going to come...
then <i>I'll</i> go!

69
00:09:34,759 --> 00:09:37,728
<i>His attacks are straight as usual...</i>

70
00:09:39,297 --> 00:09:40,059
Oh!

71
00:09:45,036 --> 00:09:47,004
Ouch!

72
00:09:48,273 --> 00:09:49,570
It's your fault!

73
00:10:02,754 --> 00:10:05,382
I... I...!

74
00:10:05,557 --> 00:10:08,117
I'm enjoying my youth!

75
00:10:12,797 --> 00:10:14,128
<i>He's too unorthodox...</i>

76
00:10:15,467 --> 00:10:16,957
<i>And most of all...he's fast!</i>

77
00:10:17,836 --> 00:10:21,101
Right in the middle of my youth...

78
00:10:30,382 --> 00:10:31,713
Dance of the Camellia!

79
00:10:38,190 --> 00:10:39,214
<i>Here!</i>

80
00:11:24,603 --> 00:11:26,366
<i>I can't read his movements...</i>

81
00:11:27,406 --> 00:11:32,400
<i>An attack on me...</i>
<i>That's quite some Taijutsu...</i>

82
00:11:33,879 --> 00:11:35,369
<i>I have no choice...</i>

83
00:11:46,959 --> 00:11:49,723
My attack ability is bones...

84
00:11:50,729 --> 00:11:53,755
You heard that earlier
from the Clone brat, right...?

85
00:11:56,101 --> 00:11:58,535
I'll sober you up right away.

86
00:11:59,137 --> 00:12:02,766
I'm... not drunk... or anything!

87
00:12:04,943 --> 00:12:06,934
Then I'll wake you up!

88
00:12:09,548 --> 00:12:11,209
I'm not drunk or anything!

89
00:12:12,084 --> 00:12:14,143
In the first place, I'm a minor!

90
00:12:16,054 --> 00:12:19,251
Minors shouldn't drink at all!

91
00:12:33,338 --> 00:12:38,867
Unorthodox, isn't it...?
This is my Kekkei Genkai.

92
00:13:00,766 --> 00:13:05,135
<i>Calm down...Think of a strategy...</i>

93
00:13:06,872 --> 00:13:10,808
<i>Seek...some kind of possibility...</i>

94
00:13:22,721 --> 00:13:25,588
<i>Humph. With that wound...</i>

95
00:13:26,091 --> 00:13:29,549
<i>It seems he wasn't able</i>
<i>to escape very far at all...</i>

96
00:13:38,937 --> 00:13:41,462
<i>This is my limit...</i>
<i>I can't move...</i>

97
00:13:49,548 --> 00:13:53,109
<i>Damn it...</i>
<i>He's already caught up?</i>

98
00:13:54,719 --> 00:13:55,981
<i>And...</i>

99
00:14:16,408 --> 00:14:18,808
My head's pounding...

100
00:14:19,478 --> 00:14:21,469
And what's with this wound...?

101
00:14:22,314 --> 00:14:25,374
It seems I was drunk, eh...?

102
00:14:27,886 --> 00:14:29,217
Your appearance...!

103
00:14:29,521 --> 00:14:35,289
It seems you've sobered up...
This is my Kekkei Genkai...

104
00:14:36,228 --> 00:14:38,321
<i>Kekkei Genkai...</i>

105
00:14:40,532 --> 00:14:46,129
My Kekkei Genkai freely controls
osteoblastic and osteoclastic cells...

106
00:14:47,139 --> 00:14:52,406
It even controls the concentration
of calcium. It's an ability to form bones.

107
00:14:52,944 --> 00:14:57,244
Basically, there are over two hundred
bones in the human body...

108
00:14:58,016 --> 00:15:01,213
But for me, that's not a set number.

109
00:15:09,594 --> 00:15:11,824
But bones are bones, after all!

110
00:15:12,063 --> 00:15:13,997
If they break, they break!

111
00:15:20,472 --> 00:15:22,201
<i>Wh-What a hardness...!</i>

112
00:15:23,475 --> 00:15:26,672
<i>Are these really human bones...?!</i>

113
00:15:29,781 --> 00:15:30,372
If so...!

114
00:15:33,185 --> 00:15:34,584
Larch Dance.

115
00:16:01,379 --> 00:16:02,573
<i>I've had it...</i>

116
00:16:03,114 --> 00:16:07,016
A little more... you clod.

117
00:16:07,886 --> 00:16:10,582
<i>It's not like the time before with Asuma...</i>

118
00:16:24,502 --> 00:16:25,434
<i>A-Asuma!</i>

119
00:16:27,172 --> 00:16:33,441
<i>There's probably zero possibility</i>
<i>of someone coming to help...</i>

120
00:16:34,813 --> 00:16:38,214
<i>Hey, what's the point of thinking</i>
<i>about someone helping...?!</i>

121
00:16:39,017 --> 00:16:40,143
<i>Calm down!</i>

122
00:17:33,705 --> 00:17:35,764
<i>The smell is moving away...</i>

123
00:17:38,943 --> 00:17:39,910
I'm saved...

124
00:17:40,845 --> 00:17:41,743
<i>Who is?</i>

125
00:17:45,850 --> 00:17:46,839
How?!

126
00:17:47,285 --> 00:17:48,775
I knew it...

127
00:17:51,823 --> 00:17:53,120
My coat?!

128
00:17:53,892 --> 00:17:58,886
It seems you didn't notice your own smell
that you're routinely used to smelling...

129
00:17:59,964 --> 00:18:02,990
With that you erased your own smell?

130
00:18:03,768 --> 00:18:10,731
You understand well the attributes of scent.
It figures why I didn't smell you.

131
00:18:12,077 --> 00:18:14,045
And... as would be expected,

132
00:18:14,112 --> 00:18:17,206
it's tough having you guys split up in two
to search for me...

133
00:18:17,582 --> 00:18:18,708
Damn it...

134
00:18:30,562 --> 00:18:32,029
Please wait!

135
00:18:33,798 --> 00:18:36,528
The real deal... is from now!

136
00:18:39,938 --> 00:18:44,966
<i>My role now is to stall this person</i>
<i>as long as possible...</i>

137
00:18:45,043 --> 00:18:49,343
<i>So, I should've avoided a big technique</i>
<i>that could be self defeating...</i>

138
00:18:51,116 --> 00:18:53,448
<i>But it seems this isn't an opponent</i>
<i>easy enough to be able to beat</i>

139
00:18:53,518 --> 00:18:55,213
<i>without using my Secret Technique...</i>

140
00:18:59,057 --> 00:18:59,921
Here I go!

141
00:19:01,693 --> 00:19:04,753
<i>I just had surgery</i>
<i>and am not at my best.</i>

142
00:19:05,230 --> 00:19:08,563
<i>But if it'd just be opening the first of the</i>
<i>Eight Inner Gates, The Gate of Opening,</i>

143
00:19:08,633 --> 00:19:09,156
<i>I should somehow...</i>

144
00:19:13,238 --> 00:19:15,365
The first gate... Gate of Opening...

145
00:19:15,940 --> 00:19:16,702
Open!

146
00:19:20,111 --> 00:19:21,840
Primary Lotus!

147
00:19:28,586 --> 00:19:31,248
<i>The impact of the kick</i>
<i>was suppressed by the bones...?!</i>

148
00:19:31,756 --> 00:19:35,920
That's some speed... But it's over.

149
00:19:36,895 --> 00:19:42,162
<i>Damn it... No matter how much I think,</i>
<i>I can't come up with any good strategies!</i>

150
00:19:43,501 --> 00:19:46,993
<i>I've had it...can't hold any further...</i>

151
00:19:49,674 --> 00:19:53,667
With me right in front of you,
you can't even howl like a loser...?

152
00:19:54,579 --> 00:19:55,238
Eh?!

153
00:19:58,983 --> 00:19:59,813
Die!

154
00:20:01,052 --> 00:20:02,144
You're mine!

155
00:20:03,321 --> 00:20:05,846
Don't you be smiling
before you're going to die!

156
00:20:17,068 --> 00:20:18,057
What?!

157
00:20:25,877 --> 00:20:27,003
Who're you?!

158
00:20:32,951 --> 00:20:36,887
Heh... It seems
you're an ally this time...

159
00:20:45,363 --> 00:20:46,022
Who're you?!

160
00:20:47,432 --> 00:20:48,797
A Sand...

161
00:20:50,235 --> 00:20:51,395
Shinobi...

162
00:20:52,437 --> 00:20:53,631
ally of the Leaf!

163
00:21:11,990 --> 00:21:14,390
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

164
00:21:14,459 --> 00:21:17,485
<i>And you smiled</i>

165
00:21:17,729 --> 00:21:19,924
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

166
00:21:19,998 --> 00:21:22,831
<i>In my own words</i>

167
00:21:22,901 --> 00:21:28,464
<i>Would you think it was</i>
<i>a bother if I approached you?</i>

168
00:21:28,573 --> 00:21:34,011
<i>Despite my doubts,</i>
<i>I worked up my courage</i>

169
00:21:34,179 --> 00:21:39,674
<i>My clumsy attempts with words</i>

170
00:21:39,785 --> 00:21:45,417
<i>You listened without turning away</i>

171
00:21:46,224 --> 00:21:51,594
<i>No wonder I get carried away by you</i>

172
00:21:51,863 --> 00:21:58,666
<i>But you don't feel anything for me, do you?</i>

173
00:21:59,071 --> 00:22:01,869
<i>I feel so sad</i>

174
00:22:01,940 --> 00:22:02,838
<i>But...</i>

175
00:22:02,908 --> 00:22:05,138
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

176
00:22:05,210 --> 00:22:08,407
<i>And you smiled</i>

177
00:22:08,480 --> 00:22:10,812
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

178
00:22:10,882 --> 00:22:14,147
<i>In my own words</i>

179
00:22:14,219 --> 00:22:16,449
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

180
00:22:16,521 --> 00:22:19,854
<i>And you smiled</i>

181
00:22:19,925 --> 00:22:22,257
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

182
00:22:22,327 --> 00:22:25,262
<i>In my own words</i>

183
00:22:25,330 --> 00:22:29,994
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

184
00:22:38,510 --> 00:22:41,308
I heard that the Sand and Leaf
had made up, but...

185
00:22:41,379 --> 00:22:43,847
It wasn't that we attacked the Leaf Village
for the fun of it.

186
00:22:43,915 --> 00:22:45,974
It was just a mission, same as this time.

187
00:22:46,051 --> 00:22:47,643
Humph! I see.

188
00:22:47,819 --> 00:22:51,585
By the way, weren't you three
headed this way together?

189
00:22:51,656 --> 00:22:54,648
We had no choice.
Since you guys are weak...

190
00:22:55,060 --> 00:22:59,622
Idiot. Don't take them lightly.
These guys are out of the ordinary.

191
00:22:59,965 --> 00:23:03,958
Next episode,
"The Sand Shinobi: Allies of the Leaf"
